Company Overview of First National Bank & Trust Company of Newtown



Snapshot People




Company Overview
First National Bank & Trust Company of Newtown, a community bank, provides personal and business banking products and services. The company offers checking accounts, savings accounts, money market accounts, individual retirement accounts, and certificates of deposit; and home equity loans, home equity lines of credit, residential and commercial mortgages, construction loans, commercial lines of credit, commercial letters of credit, business vehicle loans, and amortized loans. It also provides corporate cash management, investment services, merchant services, and wire transfers; and trust and wealth management, estate administration, trust administration, estate and financial planning, and pe...
First National Bank & Trust Company of Newtown, a community bank, provides personal and business banking products and services. The company offers checking accounts, savings accounts, money market accounts, individual retirement accounts, and certificates of deposit; and home equity loans, home equity lines of credit, residential and commercial mortgages, construction loans, commercial lines of credit, commercial letters of credit, business vehicle loans, and amortized loans. It also provides corporate cash management, investment services, merchant services, and wire transfers; and trust and wealth management, estate administration, trust administration, estate and financial planning, and personalized investment services; and online and mobile banking services. The company was founded in 1864 and is based in Newtown, Pennsylvania. It has branches in Langhorne, Richboro, Levittown, Wrightstown, Washington Crossing, Fairless Hills, Jamison, Warminster, New Hope, and Doylestown, Pennsylvania. First National Bank & Trust Company of Newtown operates as a subsidiary of FNB Bancorp, Inc.
Detailed Description


