About The First National Bank and Trust Co. of Newtown
The First National Bank and Trust Co. of Newtown was established on Feb. 25, 1864. Headquartered in Newtown, PA, it has assets in the amount of $848,638,000. Its customers are served from 17 locations. Deposits in The First National Bank and Trust Co. of Newtown are insured by FDIC.











Established On:


 
Feb. 25, 1864


 
 



FDIC Certificate Number:


 
7658


 
 



Total Assets:


 
$848,638,000


 
 



Deposit Insurance:


 
FDIC











Community Bank:


 
Yes


 
 



Institution Class:


 
Commercial bank, national (federal) charter and Fed member, supervised by the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency (OCC)

























