wtown full-time (More than 10 years)ProsIt's impossible to mention all the many reasons why I love working at "The First", but I'll try. The management team is extremely approachable and truly make time and listen to what the employees have to say. The benefits are the best around (401k match, pension plan, 100% paid health care, paid vacation time, paid holidays, college tuition reimbursement, etc.). On most occasions, FNB hires from within, so there is plenty of room for advancement and employees are encouraged to apply for new positions. If you're a honest and trustworthy person, you will have the opportunity for a lengthy career for a well respected employer. These are just a few reasons why I'm proud to say that I work at First National Bank.ConsOff the top of my head, I can not come up with a single negative remark to say about the bank.Advice to ManagementKeep doing what you're doing! You can't please all of the people all of the time, but you sure are trying!! Keep up the good work. I've been offered "better jobs" for "more money", but I can't imagine working for any other bank. You can't put a price on job security & confidence in the work place.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (0) First National Bank and Trust Company of Newtown Response seconds agoEdit • Delete First National Bank and Trust Company of Newtown 2016-10-31 10:34 PDT Oct 31, 2016"It's a great workplace."StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Customer Service Representative in Newtown, PACurrent Employee - Customer Service Representative in Newtown, PARecommendsPositive OutlookI have been working at First National Bank and Trust Company of Newtown full-time (More than 8 years)ProsBenefits package is amazing. It includes pension, 401K (matching up to 5% contribution), life insurance and completely paid health 