04/30/2016

Tracey K.

Tracey K.



    Great community bank - would never use another one!
    






  
  
            Founded in 1864, First National Bank and Trust Company of Newton is the oldest bank in Bucks County Pennsylvania. It offers a number of products and services for individuals and businesses, including checking and savings accounts, lines of credit, loans, home equity loans, mortgage services, investment services and online services. First National Bank of Newton is a community bank that operates 12 branch locations in southern and central Bucks County.
          






















